snow cave
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a cave hollowed out of snow and used for shelter.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Used elsewhere but recorded earliest in NZ: see OED snow n. 8a.  See also ice cave
